This paper is a response to an article discussing citation impact indicators in the field of computer science, which suggests that it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories. The focus on journal citation impact suggests that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category, followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computational Complexity). The discussion of citation counting methods could also be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
